  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a multicenter trial comparing laparoscopic correction of a perforated peptic ulcer
      with the open technique by upper laparotomy. Hypothesis is that after laparoscopic correction
      will be discharged 3 days sooner due to less postoperative pain and complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
